  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preventing Domestic Violence and HIV/Aids  in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project &apos;s goal still remains to reduce the social acceptance of DV in Uganda   by shifting attitudes, practices ,ideas and beliefs that perpetuate  it. Unlike the  previous projects, this project aims  to raise awareness about DV in the new areas of intervention, intergrate action   where  this work has been for over two years and  lobby  the Ministry of Gender to develope a policy to guide  implementation of the new law that was signed in April 2010.   Targets districts  will incude;  sub -ounties in Bundibugyo, Kasese, Kotido, Kaboong, and Mukono. Advocacy work  will  continue to  happen at national level.</narrative>
  </description>
